==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κριτικός]]''' (''kritikos'') "of or for judging, able to discern" < '''[[κρίσις]]''' "''[[crisis]]''"

===Verb===
'''to criticize'''  (''transitive'' or ''intransitive'')
# to [[evaluate]] (something), and [[judge]] its [[merit]]s and [[fault]]s
# to find fault (with something)

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[kritisoida]] (1,2), [[arvostella]] (1,2), [[moittia]] (2)
*Swedish: [[kritisera]] (1,2)

